-- U.S. household net worth rises to record high $81.8 trillion
-- By Michael Flaherty
-- Thu Jun 05, 2014 12:04PM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, June 5 (Reuters) - U.S. household net worth nudged up 2 percent to a new high in the first quarter, hitting a record $81.8 trillion as the stock market continued its upward climb and property values rose.

The S&P 500 <.SPX> has risen 11 percent since Feb. 5, with the Federal Reserve continuing with a highly accommodative monetary policy for a recovering U.S. economy.